 make your visit to the museum easier and more enjoyable staff are also available to answer your questions at the john l plueger family welcome center add time to your visit give yourself ample time to visit the museum lines to enter the museum parking lot tend to be longest during peak season march  august holidays weekends and on special event days please allow extra time for entry and parking   minimize carryons all visitors must pass through security screening upon entry the fewer carryon items you bring inside the museum the faster your entry and visitors behind you before you visit please review the list of prohibited items which include pocket knives and tripods visitors carrying prohibited items will not be allowed inside the museum so please leave them at home or in your car   stow your baggage the udvarhazy center has lockers in two sizes the smaller lockers accommodate small bags such as backpacks and coats the larger lockers are  wide  deep and  tall and accommodates most carryon size bags a  cent deposit is required and the quarter is returned after the key is replaced if you have baggage that does not fit in the lockers provided you will be asked to carry your bags with you   dress comfortably a visit to the smithsonian usually involves a lot of walking wear comfortable shoes and layers of clothing   connect to our wifi connecting to our wifi is easy just choose sivisitor open a web browser and accept the terms of service   go mobile learn more about the historic aircraft and space artifacts on display in the museum with stories from our experts firsthand accounts and videos of these amazing objects in flight try out copilot on your mobile device by going to copilotsiedu   no food and drink food and drink are not permitted in the museum there is no dining area beside the museum restaurant so if you bring food you must consume it outside only bottled water is permitted in the museum   please take photos you are welcome to take photos for personal use and share them on flickr however tripods monopods and selfie sticks are not permitted without prior approval for professionals please see our photography and filming policy   wheelchairs a limited number of nonmotorized wheelchairs are available on a firstcome firstserved basis please ask at the john l plueger family welcome center we do not provide strollers or motorized wheelchairs   strollers strollers are not allowed in the donald d engen observation tower you can leave your stroller in the stroller parking area outside the elevator on the ground floor   take care on ramps and overlooks the udvarhazy center has long ramps and high overlook walkways please use care and do not allow children to play on them never carry children on your shoulders   buy tickets early imax tickets can sell out during busy months or when popular films are showing we recommend you buy tickets in advance online for evening films parking is free after  pm   download and print maps  guides the museum has a limited number of printed maps to provide visitors so we recommend you print floor plans at home before coming to the museum   ask for help security officers are located throughout the building to protect the museum its collections and most importantly our visitors please feel free to ask them for assistance   first aid first aid is available please contact the nearest security officer or the john l plueger family welcome center for assistance view your favorites extended hours  national air and space museum skip to content see all topics topics science  engineering african americans aircraft apollo program art astronauts astronomers astronomy aviators awards balloons  airships business all topics top stories aviation space exploration donate now favoritesfavorites search google appliance sitewide search form search entire website by keyword leave this field blank national air and space museum visit more visit one museum two locations visit us in washington dc and chantilly va to explore 