azy center show map of northern virginia location of the udvarhazy center show map of virginia location of the udvarhazy center show map of the us established december    years ago  location chantilly virginia united states coordinates °′″n °′″w﻿  ﻿°n °w﻿    type aviation museum visitors   public transit access fairfax connector no  from wiehlereston east metro station via dulles international airport website airandspacesieduvisitudvarhazycenter the steven f udvarhazy center also called the udvarhazy center is the smithsonian national air and space museum nasms annex at washington dulles international airport in the chantilly area of fairfax county virginia united states it holds numerous exhibits including the space shuttle discovery and the enola gay the squarefoot  m facility was made possible by a  million gift in october  to the smithsonian institution by steven f udvarházy an immigrant from hungary and cofounder of the international lease finance corporation an aircraft leasing corporation the main nasm building located on the national mall in washington dc had always contained more artifacts than could be displayed and most of the collection had been stored unavailable to visitors at the paul e garber preservation restoration and storage facility in silver hill maryland a substantial addition to the center encompassing restoration conservation and collectionstorage facilities was completed in  restoration facilities and museum archives were moved from the museums garber facility to the new sections of the udvarhazy center contents  architecture and facilities  collection  events  media appearances  see also  references  external links architecture and facilitiesedit entrance view with observation tower the mary baker engen restoration hangar in january  the space shuttle discovery is in the background designed by hellmuth obata and kassabaum who also designed the national air and space museum building the center required  years of preparation and was built by hensel phelps construction co the exhibition areas comprise two large hangars the squarefoot  m boeing aviation hangar and the squarefoot  m james s mcdonnell space hangar the donald d engen observation tower provides a view of landing operations at adjacent washington dulles international airport the museum also contains an imax theater a taxiway connects the museum to the airport phase two of the udvarhazy center will be dedicated to the behindthescenes care of the smithsonians collection of aircraft spacecraft related artifacts and archival materials on december   the steven f udvarhazy center received a gift of  million for phase two from airbus americas inc — the largest corporate gift to the smithsonian institution in  the wing includes the mary baker engen restoration hangar — spacious enough to accommodate several aircraft at one time with a secondfloor viewing area designed to give visitors a behindthescenes look archives — the foremost collection of documentary records of the history science and technology of aeronautics and space flight will be housed in a single location for the first time providing researchers with ample space and equipment the emil buehler conservation laboratory — will provide conservators muchneeded space to develop and execute specialized preservation strategies for artifacts collections processing unit — a dedicated loading dock and specially designed secure area for initial inspection and analysis of artifacts air and space museum south hall the boeing  dash is also stored here collectionedit main article list of aircraft in the smithsonian institution enola gay the space shuttle discovery in the space wing of udvarhazy air france concorde fbvfa lockheed sr blackbird dassault falcon  gossamer albatross curtiss pe kittyhawk the center finished construction and opened on december   the udvarhazy center displays historic aviation and space artifacts especially items too large for the national air and space museums building on the national mall including the enola gay the boeing b superfortress which dropped the first atomic bomb on hiroshima japan the orbital spacecraft space shuttle discovery was put on public display in the james s mcdonnell space hangar on april   replacing the atmospheric test vehicle enterprise during the night of april  enterprise was loaded onto a shuttle carrier aircraft in preparation for its trip to john f kennedy international airport in new york city on april   for final destination at the intrepid sea air  space museum enterprise had been on display in the space hangar since the museum opened in  a firstgeneration tracking and data relay satellite tdrs that hangs directly above discovery the gemini vii space capsule a lockheed sr blackbird reconnaissance aircraft an air france concorde supersonic airliner a united states air force lockheed l the military version of the lockheed constellation connie airliner the boeing  dash jet transport which was the prototype for the boeing  the only surviving bell xv experimental tiltrotor craft a redstone rocket the only surviving vervillesperry m messenger the usaass first messenger aircraft the langley aerodrome a an early attempt at powered flight by smithsonian secretary samuel pierpont langley the northrop n experimental aircraft the only surviving dornier do  pfeil fighter the only surviving boeing  stratoliner the expan am clipper flying cloud one of two surviving german heinkel he  uhu night fighters the only surviving german arado ar  blitz jet bomber one of three surviving german bachem ba  natter rocketpowered interceptors the only surviving japanese nakajima jn gekko the only surviving japanese aichi ma seiran one of four surviving northrop p black widow night fighters one of two surviving boeing p peashooter fighters a bede bd singleseat homebuilt aircraft that was somewhat popular in the s j version is the smallest manned jet aircraft the beckmahoney sorceress known as the winningest racing biplane in aviation hi