oss curtiss pe kittyhawk the center finished construction and opened on december   the udvarhazy center displays historic aviation and space artifacts especially items too large for the national air and space museums building on the national mall including the enola gay the boeing b superfortress which dropped the first atomic bomb on hiroshima japan the orbital spacecraft space shuttle discovery was put on public display in the james s mcdonnell space hangar on april   replacing the atmospheric test vehicle enterprise during the night of april  enterprise was loaded onto a shuttle carrier aircraft in preparation for its trip to john f kennedy international airport in new york city on april   for final destination at the intrepid sea air  space museum enterprise had been on display in the space hangar since the museum opened in  a firstgeneration tracking and data relay satellite tdrs that hangs directly above discovery the gemini vii space capsule a lockheed sr blackbird reconnaissance aircraft an air france concorde supersonic airliner a united states air force lockheed l the military version of the lockheed constellation connie airliner the boeing  dash jet transport which was the prototype for the boeing  the only surviving bell xv experimental tiltrotor craft a redstone rocket the only surviving vervillesperry m messenger the usaass first messenger aircraft the langley aerodrome a an early attempt at powered flight by smithsonian secretary samuel pierpont langley the northrop n experimental aircraft the only surviving dornier do  pfeil fighter the only surviving boeing  stratoliner the expan am clipper flying cloud one of two surviving german heinkel he  uhu night fighters the only surviving german arado ar  blitz jet bomber one of three surviving german bachem ba  natter rocketpowered interceptors the only surviving japanese nakajima jn gekko the only surviving japanese aichi ma seiran one of four surviving northrop p black widow night fighters one of two surv